A baby boy has died after plunging from a window on the seventh floor of a block of flats. He fell to his death in Leeds, West Yorkshire, shortly after 1pm on Saturday, police have confirmed. The boy was rushed to hospital but was pronounced dead shortly afterwards as medics were unable to save him. Investigators are now trying to find out exactly what happened in the events leading to the child’s death. West Yorkshire Police said officers were called to the scene at Saville Green at around 1.25pm. In a statement, the force said the incident is being treated as a ‘sudden unexpected death in childhood’. It added: ‘We ask that people consider the family and respect their privacy at what is clearly a very difficult time for them.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.